# CLAUDE.md - Guidelines for {{ project_name }} 

## Commands
- Build: `just build` (all), `cargo build` (Rust only)
- Lint: `just check` (all), `cargo clippy` (Rust only), `just web lint` (TS/JS)
- Format: `cargo fmt` (Rust), `pnpm run format` (TS/JS), `ruff format` (Python)
- Test: `just test` (all), `cargo nextest run` (all Rust), `cargo test specific_test` (single test)
- Single module tests: `just web test`, `just python test`, `just go test`, `just go-wasm test`
- Coverage: `just cov` or `just cov-local` (more detailed)
- Watch: `just watch` or `cargo watch -x check -x test` (Rust)
- Dev server: `just web-dev` or `just web dev`

## Code Style Guidelines
- **Rust**:
  - Line length: 100 chars max
  - Indentation: 4 spaces
  - Imports: Reordered automatically with rustfmt
  - Prefer `Result` types for error handling

- **TypeScript**:
  - Use ESLint and Prettier configs
  - Prefer explicit types over `any`
  - Use async/await for async operations

- **Python**:
  - Use Ruff for linting and formatting
  - Use Pyright for type checking

- **General**:
  - Add copyright headers (checked with `just copyright-check`)
  - Write tests for all new functionality
